Trading Manager –
Coal Job (Commodity Trading) – Sudirman, Greater Jakarta Area, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Trading and Distribution
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a leading commodity trading company based in Australia. Our client provides non-banking funding for commodity trading, as well as trading the physical commodity itself. They are one of the largest importers of spices and coal from Indonesia. Our highly respected client, is seeking a coal trading professional with at least 3 – 5 years’ experience in the industry as well as knowledge and experience for market analysis the role for the job of Coal Trading Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
The winning candidate will be in charge of managing the transaction, logistics as well as conducting a feasibility study and financial analysis for the clients in coal industry. The successful applicant will report directly to the Representative Country Manager in Jakarta and matrix reporting to the Director in Singapore. The candidate will also be working closely with the Director to highlight any issues or risks in the course of his or her work, and to provide support and solutions.
The ability to communicate fluently in English is essential to this position. Our client is seeking to hire a hands-on professional with a strong character and charisma who is business-minded and able to able to adapt to the company’s culture.
Job responsibilities:
The primary goal is to develop and manage term coal purchase contracts within the Indonesia and in doing so establish the brand and business in Indonesia
Develop specific supplier solutions based on strong financing, structuring, logistics and risk mitigation capabilities.
Contribute to the group’s fundamental analysis of the physical coal market in order to determine the derivative strategy.
Ensure that all relevant information and data is communicated as quickly as possible.
Commercial management of physical execution.
Support freight and financing businesses by identifying opportunities and transferring contacts.
Support coal marketing efforts as appropriate.
Requirements:
Minimum a Bachelor Degree
3 – 5  years of experience in coal trading in Indonesia
Strong network of contacts, diversified sources of information
Good knowledge of risk management and the financial side of the business
Good command in English and Bahasa Indonesia
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.